{
  "texts": [
    "Compared with the traditional A * algorithm, the advantage of the hybrid A * algorithm is that it can be applied to the path planning problem of Ackermann model robots and commonly used vehicles, and has shown good results in lateral parking and reverse parking.",
    "However, the drawback of this algorithm is that it cannot guarantee the optimality and completeness of path planning.",
    "Real time path planning requires high computational speed.",
    "In many cases, such as a robot moving at high speed in an unknown environment, the trajectory needs to be continuously regenerated in a short period of time to avoid sudden threats.",
    "In general, path planning needs to be re planned mostly because the original path quality is poor."
  ]
}